children.label: namespaceIdToString
description:
Converts a given saved object namespace ID to its string representation. All namespace IDs have an identical string representation, with
the exception of the `undefined` namespace ID (which has a namespace string of `'default'`).

children.label: namespace
description: The namespace ID, which must be either a non-empty string or `undefined`.

children.label: namespaceStringToId
description:
Converts a given saved object namespace string to its ID representation. All namespace strings have an identical ID representation, with
the exception of the `'default'` namespace string (which has a namespace ID of `undefined`).

children.label: namespace
description: The namespace string, which must be non-empty.

children.label: createEmptyFindResponse
description: Creates an empty response for a find operation. This is only intended to be used by saved objects client wrappers.

children.label: generateId
description: Generates a random ID for a saved objects.

children.label: isRandomId
description: Validates that a saved object ID has been randomly generated.

children.label: id
description: The ID of a saved object.

children.label: getConvertedObjectId
description: Uses a single-namespace object's "legacy ID" to determine what its new ID will be after it is converted to a multi-namespace type.
signature: (namespace: string | undefined, type: string, id: string) => string

children.label: namespace
description: The namespace of the saved object before it is converted.

children.label: type
description: The type of the saved object before it is converted.

children.label: id
description: The ID of the saved object before it is converted.

returnComment: The ID of the saved object after it is converted.
